thub.com/jupyter/nbconvert/security/advisories/GHSA-xm59-rqc7-hhvf"],"description":"nbconvert has an uncontrolled search path that leads to unauthorized code execution on Windows","cvss":[{"type":"Secondary","version":"4.0","vector":"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:P/VC:H/VI:H/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N","metrics":{"baseScore":8.5},"vendorMetadata":{}}],"epss":[{"cve":"CVE-2025-53000","epss":0.00016,"percentile":0.03549,"date":"2026-05-06"}],"cwes":[{"cve":"CVE-2025-53000","cwe":"CWE-427","source":"security-advisories@github.com","type":"Secondary"}],"fix":{"versions":["7.17.0"],"state":"fixed","available":[{"version":"7.17.0","date":"2026-02-10","kind":"first-observed"}]},"advisories":[],"risk":0.012800000000000002},"relatedVulnerabilities":[{"id":"CVE-2025-53000","dataSource":"https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-53000","namespace":"nvd:cpe","severity":"High","urls":["https://github.com/jupyter/nbconvert/blob/4f61702f5c7524d8a3c4ac0d5fc33a6ac2fa36a7/nbconvert/preprocessors/svg2pdf.py#L104","https://github.com/jupyter/nbconvert/commit/c9ac1d1040459ed1ff9eb34e9918ce5a87cf9d71","https://github.com/jupyter/nbconvert/issues/2258","https://github.com/jupyter/nbconvert/releases/tag/v7.17.0","https://github.com/jupyter/nbconvert/security/advisories/GHSA-xm59-rqc7-hhvf","https://www.imperva.com/blog/code-execution-in-jupyter-notebook-exports"],"description":"The nbconvert tool, jupyter nbconvert, converts Jupyter notebooks to various other formats via Jinja templates. Versions of nbconvert up to and including 7.16.6 on Windows have a vulnerability in which converting a notebook containing SVG output to a PDF results in unauthorized code execution. Specifically, a third party can create a `inkscape.bat` file that defines a Windows batch script, capable of arbitrary code execution. When a user runs `jupyter nbconvert --to pdf` on a notebook containing SVG output to a PDF on a Windows platform from this directory, the `inkscape.bat` file is run unexpectedly. This issue has been