thub.com/jupyter/nbconvert/security/advisories/GHSA-xm59-rqc7-hhvf"],"description":"nbconvert has an uncontrolled search path that leads to unauthorized code execution on Windows","cvss":[{"type":"Secondary","version":"4.0","vector":"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:P/VC:H/VI:H/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N","metrics":{"baseScore":8.5},"vendorMetadata":{}}],"epss":[{"cve":"CVE-2025-53000","epss":0.00016,"percentile":0.03549,"date":"2026-05-06"}],"cwes":[{"cve":"CVE-2025-53000","cwe":"CWE-427","source":"security-advisories@github.com","type":"Secondary"}],"fix":{"versions":["7.17.0"],"state":"fixed","available":[{"version":"7.17.0","date":"2026-02-10","kind":"first-observed"}]},"advisories":[],"risk":0.012800000000000002},"relatedVulnerabilities":[{"id":"CVE-2025-53000","dataSource":"https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-53000","namespace":"nvd:cpe","severity":"High","urls":["https://github.com/jupyter/nbconvert/blob/4f61702f5c7524d8a3c4ac0d5fc33a6ac2fa36a7/nbconvert/preprocessors/svg2pdf.py#L104","https://github.com/jupyter/nbconvert/commit/c9ac1d1040459ed1ff9eb34e9918ce5a87cf9d71","https://github.com/jupyter/nbconvert/issues/2258","https://github.com/jupyter/nbconvert/releases/tag/v7.17.0","https://github.com/jupyter/nbconvert/security/advisories/GHSA-xm59-rqc7-hhvf","https://www.imperva.com/blog/code-execution-in-jupyter-notebook-exports"],"description":"The nbconvert tool, jupyter nbconvert, converts Jupyter notebooks to various other formats via Jinja templates. Versions of nbconvert up to and including 7.16.6 on Windows have a vulnerability in which converting a notebook containing SVG output to a PDF results in unauthorized code execution. Specifically, a third party can create a `inkscape.bat` file that defines a Windows batch script, capable of arbitrary code execution. When a user runs `jupyter nbconvert --to pdf` on a notebook containing SVG output to a PDF on a Windows platform from this directory, the `inkscape.bat` file is run unexpectedly. This issue has been patched in version 7.17.0.","cvss":[{"source":"nvd@nist.gov","type":"Primary","version":"3.1","vector":"CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:N/UI:R/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H","metrics":{"baseScore":7.8,"exploitabilityScore":1.9,"impactScore":5.9},"vendorMetadata":{}},{"source":"security-advisories@github.com","type":"Secondary","version":"4.0","vector":"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:P/VC:H/VI:H/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N/E:X/CR:X/IR:X/AR:X/MAV:X/MAC:X/MAT:X/MPR:X/MUI:X/MVC:X/MVI:X/MVA:X/MSC:X/MSI:X/MSA:X/S:X/AU:X/R:X/V:X/RE:X/U:X","metrics":{"baseScore":8.5},"vendorMetadata":{}}],"epss":[{"cve":"CVE-2025-53000","epss":0.00016,"percentile":0.03549,"date":"2026-05-06"}],"cwes":[{"cve":"CVE-2025-53000","cwe":"CWE-427","source":"security-advisories@github.com","type":"Secondary"}]}],"matchDetails":[{"type":"exact-direct-match","matcher":"python-matcher","searchedBy":{"language":"python","namespace":"github:language:python","package":{"name":"nbconvert","version":"7.16.6"}},"found":{"vulnerabilityID":"GHSA-xm59-rqc7-hhvf","versionConstraint":"<7.17.0 (python)"},"fix":{"suggestedVersion":"7.17.0"}}],"artifact":{"id":"e8deea59059279aa","name":"nbconvert","version":"7.16.6","type":"python","locations":[{"path":"/uv.lock","accessPath":"/uv.lock","annotations":{"evidence":"primary"}}],"language":"python","licenses":[],"cpes":["cpe:2.3:a:jupyter:nbconvert:7.16.6:*:*:*:*:python:*:*"],"purl":"pkg:pypi/nbconvert@7.16.6","upstreams":[]}},{"vulnerability":{"id":"GHSA-p423-j2cm-9vmq","dataSource":"https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-p423-j2cm-9vmq","namespace":"github:language:python","severity":"Medium","urls":["https://github.com/pyca/cryptography/security/advisories/GHSA-p423-j2cm-9vmq","https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-39892","http://www.openwall.com/lists/oss-security/2026/04/08/12"],"description":"Cryptography vulnerable to buffer overflow if non-contiguous buffers were passed to APIs","cvss":[{"type":"Secondary","version":"4.0","vector":"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/